data.Comments: If stung by a bee, needs shot immediately.

The comment field is large enough for, maybe two lines  worth of text. If you do not have enough room here, please go to the Notes field where there is unlimited text availability. This is a good area to place additional data about the photo.
data.Notes:
the notes field in Complaints can hold unlimited text. this is useful if you have an ongoing investigation that does not turn into an incident, which means it does not have an offense related action.  

Officers can also cut and paste into this field from other programs; such as word, excel, or notepad.  Simple right click to view the menu for cut and paste.

usually if text is long, the complaint will be turned into an Incident. Once you are in an incident there is a whole folder for atleast 12 separate supplements. 

These supplement folders each hold unlimited text as well. As stated above there is the capacity for atleast 12 separate supplements.

Each text field in Informant has spell-check available.
